Prodi wins Senate vote 
The center-left government of Romano Prodi Friday won a vote of
confidence in the Senate, a week after he presented his cabinet.
Prod 5.30 dollars per ounce.
PLATINUM and PALLADIUM: plunge. The price of these two metals plunged
by two to three dollars this week as the prospect of big sales by
Russia loomed. Platinum fell to 399 dollars per ounce and palladium
retreated to 129 dollars.
President Boris Yeltsin has approved a proposal by the Russian central
bank to begin selling from 1997 twenty tonnes of palladium (643,000
ounces) and a tonne of rhodium from the country's strategic stocks
every year.
